<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The keys are registers &#95;without&#95; subregisters. This won&#39;t allow</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// defining the &quot;other part&quot; of &quot;vreg&quot; would also count as a definition</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If a value of a pair vreg:subreg needs to be obtained, the cell for</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The required interface:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - A set of three &quot;evaluate&quot; functions. Each returns &quot;true&quot; if the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       computation succeeded, &quot;false&quot; otherwise.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   (1) Given an instruction MI, and the map with input values &quot;Inputs&quot;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="301"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       compute the set of output values &quot;Outputs&quot;. An example of when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       the computation can &quot;fail&quot; is if MI is not an instruction that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="303"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       is recognized by the evaluator.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00304" /><CodeLine lineNumber="304"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   (2) Given a register R (as reg:subreg), compute the cell that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00305" /><CodeLine lineNumber="305"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       corresponds to the &quot;subreg&quot; part of the given register.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00306" /><CodeLine lineNumber="306"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   (3) Given a branch instruction BrI, compute the set of target blocks.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00307" /><CodeLine lineNumber="307"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       If the branch can fall-through, add null (0) to the list of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00308" /><CodeLine lineNumber="308"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       possible targets.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00309" /><CodeLine lineNumber="309"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - A function &quot;rewrite&quot;, that given the cell map after propagation,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   could rewrite instruction MI in a more beneficial form. Return</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &quot;true&quot; if a change has been made, &quot;false&quot; otherwise.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-hexagonconstpropagation-cpp-/machineconstevaluator/#a2642f5609c60c3f7878b1b917e9875f4"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">using </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-hexagonconstpropagation-cpp-/machineconstevaluator/#a2642f5609c60c3f7878b1b917e9875f4">CellMap</a> = <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-hexagonconstpropagation-cpp-/machineconstpropagator/cellmap">MachineConstPropagator::CellMap</a>;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00962" /><CodeLine lineNumber="962"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MachineConstPropagator::rewrite(MachineFunction &amp;MF) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00963" /><CodeLine lineNumber="963"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/groups/arcopt/#gaa57b1a4e6a1c79233913139635169cf1">Changed</a> = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00964" /><CodeLine lineNumber="964"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Rewrite all instructions based on the collected cell information.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00965" /><CodeLine lineNumber="965"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00966" /><CodeLine lineNumber="966"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Traverse the instructions in a post-order, so that rewriting an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00967" /><CodeLine lineNumber="967"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instruction can make changes &quot;downstream&quot; in terms of control-flow</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00968" /><CodeLine lineNumber="968"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// without affecting the rewriting process. (We should not change</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00969" /><CodeLine lineNumber="969"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instructions that have not yet been visited by the rewriter.)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00970" /><CodeLine lineNumber="970"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The reason for this is that the rewriter can introduce new vregs,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00971" /><CodeLine lineNumber="971"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and replace uses of old vregs (which had corresponding cells</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00972" /><CodeLine lineNumber="972"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// computed during propagation) with these new vregs (which at this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00973" /><CodeLine lineNumber="973"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// point would not have any cells, and would appear to be &quot;top&quot;).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00974" /><CodeLine lineNumber="974"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If an attempt was made to evaluate an instruction with a fresh</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00975" /><CodeLine lineNumber="975"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &quot;top&quot; vreg, it would cause an error (abend) in the evaluator.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00976" /><CodeLine lineNumber="976"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00977" /><CodeLine lineNumber="977"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Collect the post-order-traversal block ordering. The subsequent</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00978" /><CodeLine lineNumber="978"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// traversal/rewrite will update block successors, so it&#39;s safer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00979" /><CodeLine lineNumber="979"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// if the visiting order it computed ahead of time.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00983" /><CodeLine lineNumber="983"><span class="doxyHighlight">      POT.push&#95;back(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00984" /><CodeLine lineNumber="984"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00985" /><CodeLine lineNumber="985"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (MachineBasicBlock &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a> : POT) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00986" /><CodeLine lineNumber="986"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Walk the block backwards (which usually begin with the branches).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00987" /><CodeLine lineNumber="987"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If any branch is rewritten, we may need to update the successor</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00992" /><CodeLine lineNumber="992"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Compute the successor information.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00993" /><CodeLine lineNumber="993"><span class="doxyHighlight">    SetVector&lt;const MachineBasicBlock&#42;&gt; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-textstubv5-cpp-/#ad2f3f81faa370c8bf9a1f81612c90adfa1eb7e8cfb9fedbbf4d8f497fed784976">Targets</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00994" /><CodeLine lineNumber="994"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> HaveTargets = computeBlockSuccessors(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>, Targets);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01003" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1003"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01004" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1004"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The rewriting could rewrite PHI nodes to non-PHI nodes, causing</span></CodeLine>

A1.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#a317c64fd4cfebc88e79387b3821a629d">trunc</a>(Bits) : A1.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#a1dc76cc8bf703e6ada68bededcbb9573">zext</a>(Bits);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01816" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1816"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a> &gt; 1)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01817" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1817"><span class="doxyHighlight">    LoBits = LoBits.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#a1dc76cc8bf703e6ada68bededcbb9573">zext</a>(SW);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01818" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1818"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01819" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1819"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint">APInt</a> Res(SW, 0, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01820" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1820"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> i = 0; i &lt; <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a845e08be4b0320d66901a66b0c0e9509">Count</a>; ++i) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01821" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1821"><span class="doxyHighlight">    Res &lt;&lt;= Bits;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01822" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1822"><span class="doxyHighlight">    Res |= LoBits;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01823" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1823"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01824" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1824"><span class="doxyHighlight">  Result = Res;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01825" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1825"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">true</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
